The paper focuses on image classification using deep neural networks, specifically comparing the generalization ability of CNNs and CapsNets. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new method for reducing the number of parameters in CapsNets, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models on a specific task, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
